56:10.000 --> 56:12.000
becomes larger.

56:12.000 --> 56:14.000
The next goal of the manufacturer

56:14.000 --> 56:16.000
is to attract attention

56:16.000 --> 56:18.000
to his own assortment,

56:18.000 --> 56:20.000
to his own trademark.

56:20.000 --> 56:22.000
And this is understandable

56:22.000 --> 56:24.000
because the seller says

56:24.000 --> 56:26.000
that it is important for him

56:26.000 --> 56:28.000
to optimize the assortment of the store in general,

56:28.000 --> 56:30.000
because the store provides a service

56:30.000 --> 56:32.000
for selecting an assortment,

56:32.000 --> 56:34.000
and not the only product

56:34.000 --> 56:36.000
that the buyer needs to present.

56:36.000 --> 56:38.000
The main thing is that the buyer

56:38.000 --> 56:40.000
came and found everything he needs

56:40.000 --> 56:42.000
in this selling point.

56:42.000 --> 56:44.000
Therefore, he will not pay

56:44.000 --> 56:46.000
much attention to your product.

56:46.000 --> 56:48.000
The next goal of the manufacturer

56:48.000 --> 56:50.000
is to create a competitive advantage of the product.

56:50.000 --> 56:52.000
What do we see in the seller?

56:52.000 --> 56:54.000
Of course, the creation of a competitive advantage

56:54.000 --> 56:56.000
of the store.

56:56.000 --> 56:58.000
For example, there is a wider assortment,

56:58.000 --> 57:00.000
or there are lower prices,

57:00.000 --> 57:02.000
or there is a very convenient parking,

57:02.000 --> 57:04.000
or there is a complex with a store,

57:04.000 --> 57:06.000
a cafe and an entertainment center.

57:06.000 --> 57:08.000
That is, the seller needs

57:08.000 --> 57:10.000
a competitive advantage of the store in general,

57:10.000 --> 57:12.000
and we need

57:12.000 --> 57:14.000
a competitive advantage of our product.

57:14.000 --> 57:16.000
Here our goals do not coincide.

57:16.000 --> 57:18.000
The next point is

57:18.000 --> 57:20.000
to create an attachment to the trading mark,

57:20.000 --> 57:22.000
says the manufacturer,

57:22.000 --> 57:24.000
to our trading mark.

57:24.000 --> 57:26.000
What does the seller say?

57:26.000 --> 57:28.000
He just needs an optimal assortment

57:28.000 --> 57:30.000
of well-known brands

57:30.000 --> 57:32.000
that will be visited by certain buyers.

57:32.000 --> 57:34.000
He does not care about

57:34.000 --> 57:36.000
an attachment to a particular brand,

57:36.000 --> 57:38.000
he cares about an attachment

57:38.000 --> 57:40.000
to a package of well-known brands.

57:40.000 --> 57:42.000
The next goal of the manufacturer

57:42.000 --> 57:44.000
is, of course, to avoid a situation

57:44.000 --> 57:46.000
when the product is not in the trading point.

57:46.000 --> 57:48.000
Because when your product is not there,

57:48.000 --> 57:50.000
the buyer just switches

57:50.000 --> 57:52.000
to another trading mark.

57:52.000 --> 57:54.000
For the store, of course, it is also important

57:54.000 --> 57:56.000
that the full assortment is present,

57:56.000 --> 57:58.000
but if there is no your product,

57:58.000 --> 58:00.000
then they will put another one.

58:00.000 --> 58:02.000
In general, there will be no problems.

58:02.000 --> 58:04.000
Therefore, here you yourself must make sure

58:04.000 --> 58:06.000
that your product is present in the trading point.

58:06.000 --> 58:08.000
Well, the next one is to form an attachment

58:08.000 --> 58:10.000
to the positive image of the manufacturer.

58:10.000 --> 58:12.000
Says the manufacturer,

58:12.000 --> 58:14.000
it is important for me to be well perceived.

58:14.000 --> 58:16.000
And what does the store say?

58:16.000 --> 58:18.000
The store says that it is important

58:18.000 --> 58:20.000
for the store to be perceived in general,

58:20.000 --> 58:22.000
positively,

58:22.000 --> 58:24.000
so that there are flexible conditions,

58:24.000 --> 58:26.000
for example, in terms of working time,

58:26.000 --> 58:28.000
for example, up to the last buyer,

58:28.000 --> 58:30.000
or something like that.

58:30.000 --> 58:32.000
That is, the store is naturally important

58:32.000 --> 58:34.000
in general,

58:34.000 --> 58:36.000
and our trading mark is important to us.

58:36.000 --> 58:38.000
And these things need to be taken into account

58:38.000 --> 58:40.000
when we develop the standard of merchandising

58:40.000 --> 58:42.000
and offer our product

58:42.000 --> 58:44.000
to the trading point.

58:44.000 --> 58:46.000
Let's consider the main tasks

58:46.000 --> 58:48.000
of the company's merchandising.

58:48.000 --> 58:50.000
What should you pay attention to

58:50.000 --> 58:52.000
when you develop a standard

58:52.000 --> 58:54.000
or when you determine the product schedule?

58:54.000 --> 58:56.000
What should you take into account?

58:56.000 --> 58:58.000
The first is the minimum set

58:58.000 --> 59:00.000
of assortment positions,

59:00.000 --> 59:02.000
or they also call it SKU.

59:02.000 --> 59:04.000
Roughly speaking, one unit of the assortment.

59:04.000 --> 59:06.000
That is, how many of you

59:06.000 --> 59:08.000
should have the layout of this assortment

59:08.000 --> 59:10.000
so that your layout

59:10.000 --> 59:12.000
looks high-quality and good.

59:12.000 --> 59:14.000
The next task

59:14.000 --> 59:16.000
is the place where your product is placed.

59:16.000 --> 59:18.000
You must determine the category

59:18.000 --> 59:20.000
in which department your product is placed

59:20.000 --> 59:22.000
and in which place of the store.

59:22.000 --> 59:24.000
The next task

59:24.000 --> 59:26.000
is the number of additional sales places.

59:26.000 --> 59:28.000
This is very important

59:28.000 --> 59:30.000
because additional sales places

59:30.000 --> 59:32.000
give the opportunity

59:32.000 --> 59:34.000
for additional acquaintance with your product.

59:34.000 --> 59:36.000
And, of course,

59:36.000 --> 59:38.000
your most popular product is placed there,

59:38.000 --> 59:40.000
which greatly increases sales.

59:40.000 --> 59:42.000
You must determine in advance

59:42.000 --> 59:44.000
where it is possible to place additional places.

59:44.000 --> 59:46.000
Next, you must determine

59:46.000 --> 59:48.000
the number of SKU,

59:48.000 --> 59:50.000
how many assortment units

59:50.000 --> 59:52.000
of the product are placed

59:52.000 --> 59:54.000
and the order of their placement.

59:54.000 --> 59:56.000
For example, from light to dark,

59:56.000 --> 59:58.000
from the lowest price to the highest,

59:58.000 --> 01:00:00.000
from the lowest fat to the highest,

01:00:00.000 --> 01:00:02.000
and so on.

01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:04.000
That is, the order can be different

01:00:04.000 --> 01:00:06.000
depending on the product,

01:00:06.000 --> 01:00:08.000
if the product is placed from light to dark,

01:00:08.000 --> 01:00:10.000
or a combination of colors,

01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:12.000
or a joint purchase.

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:14.000
That is, the rules can be different,

01:00:14.000 --> 01:00:16.000
there are a lot of them,

01:00:16.000 --> 01:00:18.000
but you must immediately

01:00:18.000 --> 01:00:20.000
determine by standards

01:00:20.000 --> 01:00:22.000
what rules you set this product.

01:00:22.000 --> 01:00:24.000
The next point is the number of positions

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:26.000
or they also call it facing.

01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:28.000
Look, an assortment is an assortment unit.

01:00:28.000 --> 01:00:30.000
For example, you decided

01:00:30.000 --> 01:00:32.000
that you will put

01:00:32.000 --> 01:00:34.000
three office chairs,

01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:36.000
but these three office chairs

01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:38.000
can be repeated, right?

01:00:38.000 --> 01:00:40.000
And SKU will be three,

01:00:40.000 --> 01:00:42.000
because there are three different types.

01:00:42.000 --> 01:00:44.000
And facing is how many chairs there will be.

01:00:44.000 --> 01:00:46.000
Roughly speaking,

01:00:46.000 --> 01:00:48.000
if you put each SKU in two positions,

01:00:48.000 --> 01:00:50.000
then the facing will be equal to six.

01:00:50.000 --> 01:00:52.000
The next thing to determine

01:00:52.000 --> 01:00:54.000
is the product supply

01:00:54.000 --> 01:00:56.000
or the minimum load.

01:00:56.000 --> 01:00:58.000
The product supply should be

01:00:58.000 --> 01:01:00.000
such that it is constantly present

01:01:00.000 --> 01:01:02.000
on the shelf of the store,

01:01:02.000 --> 01:01:04.000
taking into account that it leaves

01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:06.000
this shelf.

01:01:06.000 --> 01:01:08.000
That is, a certain supply

01:01:08.000 --> 01:01:10.000
should always be in the store.

01:01:10.000 --> 01:01:12.000
The next point is positioning

01:01:12.000 --> 01:01:14.000
the price relative to the competitors.

01:01:14.000 --> 01:01:16.000
That is, you must immediately determine

01:01:16.000 --> 01:01:18.000
what price category your product is in,

01:01:18.000 --> 01:01:20.000
because different price categories

01:01:20.000 --> 01:01:22.000
are distributed differently,

01:01:22.000 --> 01:01:24.000
and actually where this product

01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:26.000
will be located,

01:01:26.000 --> 01:01:28.000
next to which competitors,

01:01:28.000 --> 01:01:30.000
and what is the recommended price

01:01:30.000 --> 01:01:32.000
for this product, it is different.

01:01:32.000 --> 01:01:34.000
Therefore, we must clearly determine

01:01:34.000 --> 01:01:36.000
what the price will be for us.

01:01:36.000 --> 01:01:38.000
The next point, which is often determined

01:01:38.000 --> 01:01:40.000
by very famous manufacturers,

01:01:40.000 --> 01:01:42.000
is the share relative to the competitors

01:01:42.000 --> 01:01:44.000
of your product.

01:01:44.000 --> 01:01:46.000
For example, you say that the share

01:01:46.000 --> 01:01:48.000
of our office chairs should be 50%

01:01:48.000 --> 01:01:50.000
relative to competitors,

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:52.000
that is, half of the category should be

01:01:52.000 --> 01:01:54.000
occupied by us.

01:01:54.000 --> 01:01:56.000
This is, of course, an ambitious goal,

01:01:56.000 --> 01:01:58.000
but nevertheless, such goals are set

01:01:58.000 --> 01:02:00.000
and there are two more points

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:02.000
that we must talk about.

01:02:02.000 --> 01:02:04.000
This is, of course, the placement of price tags.

01:02:04.000 --> 01:02:06.000
A clear and competent design

01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:08.000
and where they are placed.

01:02:08.000 --> 01:02:10.000
In some stores there are standards

01:02:10.000 --> 01:02:12.000
for price tags, and this is great,

01:02:12.000 --> 01:02:14.000
but in some stores they simply

01:02:14.000 --> 01:02:16.000
do not comply, so where and how

01:02:16.000 --> 01:02:18.000
we place them must be necessarily

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:20.000
agreed upon in the standard of merchandising.

01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:22.000
And the last point is the schedule itself.

01:02:22.000 --> 01:02:24.000
That is, we must draw out how,

01:02:24.000 --> 01:02:26.000
where and why our product is,

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:28.000
so that the merchandiser does not invent

01:02:28.000 --> 01:02:30.000
and do not compose and do not fantasize

01:02:30.000 --> 01:02:32.000
how to put it,

01:02:32.000 --> 01:02:34.000
how it will be better, how it will be worse.

01:02:34.000 --> 01:02:36.000
We must give him a clear instruction

01:02:36.000 --> 01:02:38.000
so that he does not touch it.

01:02:38.000 --> 01:02:40.000
Only this will ensure you

01:02:40.000 --> 01:02:42.000
increased sales and efficiency

01:02:42.000 --> 01:02:44.000
of this tool.

01:02:44.000 --> 01:02:46.000
All the basic rules of merchandising

01:02:46.000 --> 01:02:48.000
will be described in your lecture material,

01:02:48.000 --> 01:02:50.000
which will help you to form

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:52.000
the right schedule

01:02:52.000 --> 01:02:54.000
and the standard of merchandising.

01:02:54.000 --> 01:02:56.000
There are three groups of these rules.

01:02:56.000 --> 01:02:58.000
This is the location, presentation

01:02:58.000 --> 01:03:00.000
and stock.

01:03:00.000 --> 01:03:02.000
You can decode all of them there,

01:03:02.000 --> 01:03:04.000
look at them,

01:03:04.000 --> 01:03:06.000
determine the rules of the layout

01:03:06.000 --> 01:03:08.000
and, in fact,

01:03:08.000 --> 01:03:10.000
create your own standard of merchandising

01:03:10.000 --> 01:03:12.000
according to the image and likeness.

01:03:12.000 --> 01:03:14.000
And about the location itself,

01:03:14.000 --> 01:03:16.000
I would like to say a few more words

01:03:16.000 --> 01:03:18.000
and show you the hot and cold

01:03:18.000 --> 01:03:20.000
zones in the store

01:03:20.000 --> 01:03:22.000
to understand where you can

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:24.000
put the products and where not.

01:03:24.000 --> 01:03:26.000
Here is the image.

01:03:26.000 --> 01:03:28.000
You can see that

01:03:28.000 --> 01:03:30.000
all 100% of the products

01:03:30.000 --> 01:03:32.000
that enter the store

01:03:32.000 --> 01:03:34.000
only 90% of them

01:03:34.000 --> 01:03:36.000
are in the first square.

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:38.000
The rest 10% take what they need

01:03:38.000 --> 01:03:40.000
and go to the checkout or return

01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:42.000
after leaving the store.

01:03:42.000 --> 01:03:44.000
Then, during the movement,

01:03:44.000 --> 01:03:46.000
only 70% pass.

01:03:46.000 --> 01:03:48.000
The rest 20% have already taken

01:03:48.000 --> 01:03:50.000
the product and went to the checkout.

01:03:50.000 --> 01:03:52.000
Only 50% pass.

01:03:52.000 --> 01:03:54.000
And at the end of the store,

01:03:54.000 --> 01:03:56.000
that is, the entire cycle of the store

01:03:56.000 --> 01:03:58.000
only 30%.

01:03:58.000 --> 01:04:00.000
You see how the number of buyers

01:04:00.000 --> 01:04:02.000
that pass the whole hall decreases.

01:04:02.000 --> 01:04:04.000
This, of course, reduces

01:04:04.000 --> 01:04:06.000
the efficiency of sales.

01:04:06.000 --> 01:04:08.000
And that square where the buyer

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:10.000
is only 30% is the lower left square.

01:04:10.000 --> 01:04:12.000
It is considered the most

01:04:12.000 --> 01:04:14.000
ineffective, it is considered

01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:16.000
the cold zone of the store.

01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:18.000
If your product is located in this zone,

01:04:18.000 --> 01:04:20.000
then you will not be surprised

01:04:20.000 --> 01:04:22.000
why your sales are so small.

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:24.000
How to avoid this?

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:26.000
You can highlight something bright,

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:28.000
you can put large figures,

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:30.000
additional lighting,

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:32.000
any bright things that will attract

01:04:32.000 --> 01:04:34.000
the attention of the buyer

01:04:34.000 --> 01:04:36.000
and make them go further.

01:04:36.000 --> 01:04:38.000
Remember the location of supermarkets.

01:04:38.000 --> 01:04:40.000
In this department, most often,

01:04:40.000 --> 01:04:42.000
there is bread and, moreover, it is baked there.

01:04:42.000 --> 01:04:44.000
The smell, the aroma of bread

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:46.000
makes us go there

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:48.000
like Pavlov's dog.

01:04:48.000 --> 01:04:50.000
It makes us go through

01:04:50.000 --> 01:04:52.000
most of the store.

01:04:52.000 --> 01:04:54.000
That is why departments are placed

01:04:54.000 --> 01:04:56.000
in this way.

01:04:56.000 --> 01:04:58.000
Also, on the slide you have

01:04:58.000 --> 01:05:00.000
the rules of the golden triangle.

01:05:00.000 --> 01:05:02.000
The location of the golden triangle

01:05:02.000 --> 01:05:04.000
consists of three parts.

01:05:04.000 --> 01:05:06.000
The first is the entrance,

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:08.000
the second point is the cash desk

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:10.000
and the third point is the department

01:05:10.000 --> 01:05:12.000
that is most often visited by

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:14.000
the buyer.

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:16.000
It is a department of milk and meat.

01:05:16.000 --> 01:05:18.000
Daily products are sold there

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:20.000
that the buyer

01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:22.000
has come for.

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:26.000
If you are a manufacturer,

01:05:26.000 --> 01:05:28.000
your task is to get into

01:05:28.000 --> 01:05:30.000
the zone of the golden triangle

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:32.000
because when you get into

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:34.000
the zone, your sales

01:05:34.000 --> 01:05:36.000
increase by at least 80%.

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:38.000
Most often, the buyers

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:40.000
pass there.

01:05:40.000 --> 01:05:42.000
And the task of the store itself

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:44.000
is to make the most popular

01:05:44.000 --> 01:05:46.000
departments, cash desk and entrance

01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:48.000
at a distance.

01:05:48.000 --> 01:05:50.000
Thus, it expands the field

01:05:50.000 --> 01:05:52.000
of active activity of the buyers

01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:54.000
and the zone of active purchases.

01:05:54.000 --> 01:05:56.000
Well,

01:05:56.000 --> 01:05:58.000
let's move on to the stimulation

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:00.000
of end users.

01:06:00.000 --> 01:06:02.000
Not all companies

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:04.000
are engaged in this.

01:06:04.000 --> 01:06:06.000
Nevertheless,

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:08.000
it is an expensive process,

01:06:08.000 --> 01:06:10.000
but it is very necessary

01:06:10.000 --> 01:06:12.000
because the client can leave us

01:06:12.000 --> 01:06:14.000
to other intermediaries

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:16.000
if our discount does not suit him.

01:06:16.000 --> 01:06:18.000
And end users are more loyal.

01:06:18.000 --> 01:06:20.000
If they liked our products,

01:06:20.000 --> 01:06:22.000
they will return to us

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:24.000
and buy from us

01:06:24.000 --> 01:06:26.000
and provide us with

01:06:26.000 --> 01:06:28.000
this or that income.

01:06:28.000 --> 01:06:30.000
So, when we stimulate

01:06:30.000 --> 01:06:32.000
end users,

01:06:32.000 --> 01:06:34.000
the main goal is, of course,

01:06:34.000 --> 01:06:36.000
to increase the volume of sales.

01:06:36.000 --> 01:06:38.000
But you can increase the volume of sales

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:40.000
according to the scheme.

01:06:40.000 --> 01:06:42.000
At least,

01:06:42.000 --> 01:06:44.000
the increase of sales

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:46.000
is divided into two parts

01:06:46.000 --> 01:06:48.000
 loyalty and trial purchases.

01:06:48.000 --> 01:06:50.000
Trial purchases are more

01:06:50.000 --> 01:06:52.000
related to the new product,

01:06:52.000 --> 01:06:54.000
and loyalty is related to the existing product,

01:06:54.000 --> 01:06:56.000
to the maintenance of the reliability

01:06:56.000 --> 01:06:58.000
and loyalty of our product.

01:06:58.000 --> 01:07:00.000
These two groups are divided

01:07:00.000 --> 01:07:02.000
into goals.

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:04.000
Additionally, trial purchases

01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:06.000
are divided into two parts 

01:07:06.000 --> 01:07:08.000
the availability of the product,

01:07:08.000 --> 01:07:10.000
that is, the person should want to buy it,

01:07:10.000 --> 01:07:12.000
and availability,

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:14.000
he should find a place where it is sold.

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:16.000
And loyalty is divided into three parts 

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:18.000
the frequency of purchase,

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:20.000
how often they buy,

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:22.000
adherence,

01:07:22.000 --> 01:07:24.000
do they buy our brand all the time,

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:26.000
and the possibility

01:07:26.000 --> 01:07:28.000
or frequency of switching

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:30.000
from the brand of competitors

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:32.000
to our brand.

01:07:32.000 --> 01:07:34.000
