01:46:44.000 --> 01:46:46.000
Here are the basic formulas.

01:46:46.000 --> 01:46:48.000
The first formula is the formula of profitability.

01:46:48.000 --> 01:46:50.000
Everyone knows it.

01:46:50.000 --> 01:46:52.000
When we take the additional sales,

01:46:52.000 --> 01:46:54.000
the amount of additional sales,

01:46:54.000 --> 01:46:56.000
subtract the cost of the product

01:46:56.000 --> 01:46:58.000
that we additionally sold

01:46:58.000 --> 01:47:00.000
and the costs of the event itself

01:47:00.000 --> 01:47:02.000
and divide it all by the costs,

01:47:02.000 --> 01:47:04.000
you get the coefficient.

01:47:04.000 --> 01:47:06.000
If this coefficient is less than one,

01:47:06.000 --> 01:47:08.000
your share was loss.

01:47:08.000 --> 01:47:10.000
If it is equal to one,

01:47:10.000 --> 01:47:12.000
your share has passed zero.

01:47:12.000 --> 01:47:14.000
Roughly speaking,

01:47:14.000 --> 01:47:16.000
how much you received

01:47:16.000 --> 01:47:18.000
and how much you spent.

01:47:18.000 --> 01:47:20.000
But if your share

01:47:20.000 --> 01:47:22.000
has a coefficient of more than one,

01:47:22.000 --> 01:47:24.000
you have already worked

01:47:24.000 --> 01:47:26.000
for the profit of the company.

01:47:26.000 --> 01:47:28.000
Naturally, the higher the coefficient,

01:47:28.000 --> 01:47:30.000
the better.

01:47:30.000 --> 01:47:32.000
It can be 2, 3, 4, 5, etc.

01:47:32.000 --> 01:47:34.000
It is ideal.

01:47:34.000 --> 01:47:36.000
The more, the better.

01:47:36.000 --> 01:47:38.000
The main thing is that it is more than one.

01:47:38.000 --> 01:47:40.000
Then your share worked effectively.

01:47:40.000 --> 01:47:42.000
And one more formula

01:47:42.000 --> 01:47:44.000
