01:48:00.000 --> 01:48:02.000
100,000 additional rubles.

01:48:02.000 --> 01:48:04.000
But how much you spent

01:48:04.000 --> 01:48:06.000
from this amount

01:48:06.000 --> 01:48:08.000
should be determined.

01:48:08.000 --> 01:48:10.000
That is, not the share of the total turnover

01:48:10.000 --> 01:48:12.000
because the total could be sold

01:48:12.000 --> 01:48:14.000
without the share.

01:48:14.000 --> 01:48:16.000
But how much additional income

01:48:16.000 --> 01:48:18.000
you spent is important.

01:48:18.000 --> 01:48:20.000
It shows how much additional money

01:48:20.000 --> 01:48:22.000
you earned for the owner.

01:48:22.000 --> 01:48:24.000
And this formula works

01:48:24.000 --> 01:48:26.000
very well and effectively.

01:48:26.000 --> 01:48:28.000
It shows what your owner

01:48:28.000 --> 01:48:30.000
wants to see.

01:48:30.000 --> 01:48:32.000
This is what you calculate.

01:48:32.000 --> 01:48:34.000
You take all the costs

01:48:34.000 --> 01:48:36.000
that you spent on the share.

01:48:36.000 --> 01:48:38.000
Divide it by the additional income

01:48:38.000 --> 01:48:40.000
that you received

01:48:40.000 --> 01:48:42.000
and multiply it by 100%.

01:48:42.000 --> 01:48:44.000
You get a share of the costs

01:48:44.000 --> 01:48:46.000
in the additional income.

01:48:46.000 --> 01:48:48.000
Note, not in the total, but in the additional.

01:48:48.000 --> 01:48:50.000
This is how you can calculate

01:48:50.000 --> 01:48:52.000
the share.

